Subject: Expense reports
********************************************

If you would like assistance with expense reports but have not yet designated me as your admin, please log into XMS and make the necessary change.  Also, please change your designated Manager, if necessary.   If you have any questions, give me a call at 7698.   Thanks !!!

https://expensexms.enron.com

Designating an Administrative Assistant
To designate an Administrative Assistant:
Click My Info.
On the My Info page, select the Concur Expense tab.
From the contents area on the left, choose Workflow.
In the Administrative Assistant area of the Workflow page, click the Search button .
On the Search Employee page, enter the first or last name of the assistant. (Kathryn Sheppard)
Click Find to display the search results.
In the search results area, click the name of the employee you want to designate as your assistant.
The name you selected appears in the Administrative Assistant area of the Workflow page.
On the Workflow page, click Save to save the new information.
Note If you are an administrative assistant, depending on your company settings, you may not be able to submit an expense report for your manager. If you try, you will receive a message that alerts you to this. If you do not receive a message, then you may submit the expense report for your manager.
Removing an Administrative Assistant
If you previously designated an Administrative Assistant, the name of that person appears in the Administrative Assistant area of the Workflow page.
To remove an Administrative Assistant:
On the Workflow page, click the Clear button located next to the Administrative Assistant text box.
Click Save to save the changes

